      "id": "surface_chemistry-adsorption-isotherm-analysis",
      "name": "Langmuir Adsorption Isotherm",
      "description": "The Langmuir model treats adsorption as molecules occupying a finite set of equivalent surface sites: molecules that strike an empty site adsorb, adsorption and desorption reach equilibrium, and coverage follows theta = KP/(1+KP), saturating at a monolayer.",
